ce:section.ce:para:
In this paper, the Z-scan nonlinear optical measuring instrument of Suzhou Micro-Nano Laser Photonics Technology Co., ltd. is used to test the nonlinear optics of the sample (Scheme 2
                           ). The laser wavelength is 532 nm, the pulse width is 7 ns, the frequency is 10 Hz, laser beam was focused by a 40 cm focal length lens and these operating conditions produced an intensity of 3.16 × 107 W cm−2 in 35 μm beam waist radius at the focal point. In this configuration, z0 = πω0
                           2/λ = 7.23 mm. The sample is placed in a quartz sample cell with a thickness of 2 mm, placed on a movable stage, and moved within −50 mm to 50 mm from the focus.
